The paper focuses on evaluating the accuracy of ROI evaluations in the context of information systems implementations, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The study also involves analytical expressions and Monte Carlo simulations, which are related to computational complexity (cs.CY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the estimation of intangible benefits, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
